statements.sql: select * from `users` where `id` = 1 limit 1
select * from `uploads` where `uuid` = '39d2742f-1b8f-4157-ab02-b1e599f2254c'
select * from `media` where `media`.`model_id` = 2 and `media`.`model_id` is not null and `media`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\Upload'

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'
select * from `restaurants` where `restaurants`.`id` = '10' limit 1

select * from `users` where exists (select * from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `users`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`model_id` and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User' and `name` = 'manager')

select * from `users` where exists (select * from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `users`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`model_id` and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User' and `name` = 'driver')
select `name`, `id` from `cuisines`
select `users`.`id` from `users` inner join `user_restaurants` on `users`.`id` = `user_restaurants`.`user_id` where `user_restaurants`.`restaurant_id` = 10
select `users`.`id` from `users` inner join `driver_restaurants` on `users`.`id` = `driver_restaurants`.`user_id` where `driver_restaurants`.`restaurant_id` = 10
select `cuisines`.`id` from `cuisines` inner join `restaurant_cuisines` on `cuisines`.`id` = `restaurant_cuisines`.`cuisine_id` where `restaurant_cuisines`.`restaurant_id` = 10
select * from `vendors`
select `working_days` from `restaurants` where `id` = '10'

select * from `custom_field_values` where `custom_field_values`.`customizable_id` = 10 and `custom_field_values`.`customizable_id` is not null and `custom_field_values`.`customizable_type` = 'App\Models\Restaurant'
select * from `custom_fields` where `custom_field_model` = 'App\Models\Restaurant'
select * from `media` where `media`.`model_id` = 10 and `media`.`model_id` is not null and `media`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\Restaurant'
select `role_id` from `users` where `id` = '1' limit 1
select count(`id`) as aggregate from `notifications` where `not_admin_status` = 0
select * from `media` where `media`.`model_id` = 1 and `media`.`model_id` is not null and `media`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'
select `role_id` from `users` where `id` = '1' limit 1
select count(*) as aggregate from `orders` where `manager_id` = '1' and `ManagerorderView_status` = '0'
select count(*) as aggregate from `orders` where `AdminorderView_status` = '0'

select count(*) as aggregate from `orders` inner join `restaurants` on `restaurants`.`id` = `orders`.`restaurant_id` inner join `users` on `users`.`email` = `restaurants`.`email` where `users`.`id` = '1' and `RestaurantorderView_status` = '0'
select count(*) as aggregate from `support` where `support_status` = '0'
